# Part 4B-2 - Integrating Jenkins with the Kubernetes Cluster

In this section, we will integrate the Jenkins server with the Kubernetes cluster so that Jenkins can deploy applications directly to Kubernetes.

At the end of this section, Jenkins will be able to:

- Connect to the Kubernetes API Server
- Execute `kubectl` commands
- Deploy applications to Kubernetes
- Perform rolling updates
- Verify deployments

---

# Integration Architecture

```text
                     Jenkins Server
                ┌─────────────────────┐
                │      Jenkins        │
                │---------------------│
                │ kubectl             │
                │ kubeconfig          │
                │ Docker              │
                └─────────┬───────────┘
                          │
                 Kubernetes API Server
                     Port 6443
                          │
                          ▼
               Kubernetes Control Plane
                          │
         ┌────────────────┴────────────────┐
         ▼                                 ▼
   Worker Node 1                     Worker Node 2
```

