## Checkout Source Code

Downloads the latest application source code from GitHub.

---

## Verify Workspace

Displays the Jenkins workspace.

Commands

```bash
pwd

ls -lrt
```

---

## Build Docker Image

Creates the Docker image.

Example

```
demoproject/flask-app:15
```

Also creates

```
latest
```

tag.

---

## Docker Login

Logs into Docker Hub using Jenkins Credentials.

Credentials

```
dockerhub-creds
```

---

## Push Docker Image

Uploads

```
BUILD_NUMBER
```

and

```
latest
```

to Docker Hub.

---

## Verify Kubernetes Cluster

Verifies Jenkins can communicate with Kubernetes.

```bash
kubectl get nodes
```

---

## Deploy Application

This stage contains intelligent deployment logic.

### First Deployment

If the deployment does not exist,

Jenkins automatically executes

```bash
kubectl apply -f kubernetes/namespace.yaml

kubectl apply -f kubernetes/deployment.yaml

kubectl apply -f kubernetes/service.yaml
```

Then updates the image

```bash
kubectl set image deployment/flask-deployment \
flask=$IMAGE_NAME:$TAG
```

---

### Rolling Update

If the Deployment already exists,

Jenkins skips the YAML creation and executes

```bash
kubectl set image deployment/flask-deployment \
flask=$IMAGE_NAME:$TAG
```

This performs a Rolling Update.

---

## Wait For Rollout

Jenkins waits until the deployment becomes healthy.

```bash
kubectl rollout status deployment/flask-deployment \
--timeout=300s
```

---

## Verify Deployment

Displays

Deployments

Pods

Services

Running Docker Image

