# Common Errors

## Deployment Not Found

This occurs when the deployment has never been created.

The pipeline automatically fixes this by executing

```
kubectl apply
```

before

```
kubectl set image
```

---

## ImagePullBackOff

Verify

- Docker image exists
- Docker image name matches deployment.yaml
- Docker Hub repository is public or imagePullSecrets are configured

---

## Rollout Timeout

Check

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
```

Check events

```bash
kubectl get events
```

---

## kubectl set image Failed

Verify

```bash
kubectl get deployment
```

Confirm the deployment name is

```
flask-deployment
```

