# Production Best Practices

✔ Store all secrets in Jenkins Credentials.

✔ Use Docker Hub Access Tokens instead of passwords.

✔ Protect the `main` branch with pull requests.

✔ Enable webhook authentication and HTTPS.

✔ Keep Kubernetes manifests under version control.

✔ Tag Docker images with immutable versions.

✔ Never deploy the `latest` tag in production.

✔ Use Rolling Updates with readiness and liveness probes.

✔ Use resource requests and limits for all containers.

✔ Enable monitoring with Prometheus and Grafana.

✔ Configure Alertmanager for production alerts.

✔ Use RBAC and ServiceAccounts instead of the Kubernetes admin kubeconfig for Jenkins in production.

